gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Raptors 123, Spurs 116
gameRecap.excerpt: The Raptors defeated the Spurs, 123-116, in overtime. Scottie Barnes notched a season-high 30 points (five 3PT FG) to go along with 11 rebounds, six assists, three steals, and three blocks while OG Anunoby added 24 points, including a career-high seven 3PT FG, seven rebounds, and four assists. Victor Wembanyama led San Antonio with 20 points, nine rebounds, five blocks, and four assists as Keldon Johnson totaled 26 points, six rebounds, and three assists. Toronto improves to 3-4 as San Antonio moves to 3-3.
